column2: Clear- frost last night- and no wind.
Saw wood duck- eagle- and a beaver.  Nice day with no wind.
Partly sunny- 1 3/4" of rain on July 25th.
Fog in the early am- sunny and light wind.
Light southeast wind- clear- and the temperature is 65 degrees.
Calm water- sunny- and the temperature is 75 degrees.
Sunny and the temperature is 78 degrees.
Cool- calm water- the temperature is 59 degrees- and haze with sun.
Clean.  69 degrees F.  West wind lite.  No wildlife visible.
Lake is bad - 80 degrees F- hot.  Algae very high. Other scum on water.  Heavy on shorelines.
66 degrees F.  Clear skies.  No wind.  1 heron sighted.  Worst lake conditions I have seen since 1994.
overcast day 55 degrees light waves water very high
75 degrees calm day Partly cloudy lake looks pretty good today
days have been hot much scum on water calm day
Clear day- 67 F. No wind. Overall condition of Little Trade Lake this year is not getting any better.  Weed and scum everywhere.  Very heavy with float weeds.
